    "about": "Aker BP ASA is Norway's second-largest crude oil exploration and production company, focused exclusively on the Norwegian Continental Shelf (NCS). The company was created in 2016 when Det norske oljeselskap (founded 2001) merged with BP Norge, with Aker ASA (40%), BP (30%), and public shareholders (30%) as the main owners. Headquartered in Lysaker with offices in Trondheim, Stavanger, Harstad, and Sandnessjøen, Aker BP operates six field centres: Valhall, Ula, Edvard Grieg/Ivar Aasen, Alvheim, and Skarv. The company employs over 2,400 staff. For 2025, Aker BP reported record operating cash flow of $7 billion, production guidance of 370,000–400,000 boepd for 2026, and a dividend increasing 5% to $2.65/share. CEO since 2014 is Karl Johnny Hersvik.",
